article.headline: Chattanooga 62, Elon 59
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) -- Casey Long hit a field goal and two free throws down the stretch as Chattanooga held off Elon for a 62-59 win Monday night. Long tied the game 59-59 on a jumper with 1:03 left, and later hit two free throws for the final score. Khalil Hartwell also hit a late free throw for Chattanooga (14-16, 6-11 Southern Conference). Long led the Mocs with 12 points and Keddric Mays scored 10 but was just 3-of-12 from the field. Chris Chalko scored 17 for the Phoenix (6-21, 4-12) on 6-of-8 shooting from the floor. Reserve Devan Carter had 11. Chattanooga would have won by more but hit just 17-of-32 free throws. Elon was 7-of-9. The Phoenix shot 52.4 percent including 8-of-15 3-pointers, but made 17 turnovers to Chattanooga's 7. The Mocs hit 40.8 percent. Elon led at halftime 28-25.
